## §5. INTEGRATION — K1 SURVIVAL WIRE

Per `src/cells/kernel/survival-cell/survival-cell.cell.anc` passport (commit cf74423):

```
survival-cell.decide(rate, queue, memory, cpu)
  ↓
  Qiint2Engine.getSurvivalThresholds() → [0.95, 0.85, 0.80]
  ↓
  Compare current state vs thresholds
  ↓
  Return: ACCEPT | BACKPRESSURE | LOAD_SHED | CIRCUIT_BREAK
```

**5 components cua K1 (survival-cell impl)** dua tren qiint2 params:

| Component | Source param |
|---|---|
| `BackPressureGuard.health()` | `dos_thresholds[0]` = 0.95 |
| `RateLimitGuard` (system-wide) | `tolerance_bridge_v2` = 0.30 (rate std) |
| `QueueDepthMonitor.threshold()` | `dos_thresholds[1]` = 0.85 |
| `LoadShedFallback` (priority) | `dos_thresholds[1]` + persona weights |
| `CircuitBreaker` (half-open) | `dos_thresholds[2]` = 0.80 + `snapshot_tau_decay` |

**Key insight:** 5 components share **1 source of truth** (Qiint2Engine). Update param → ALL components update. No scatter constants.

